dcterms:description: The UNSW-NB15 dataset consists of network packets with 49 features, including synthetic contemporary attack behaviors and real modern normal activity packets. It contains nine types of network attacks including Backdoors, Generic, Analysis, Shellcode, Dos, Fuzzers, Worms, Reconnaissance, and Exploits.
dcterms:title: UNSW-NB15

dcterms:description: The NSL-KDD dataset is an improved version of the KDD CUP99 dataset, which aims to solve the inherent problems of the KDD CUP99 datasets through collecting data from the DARPA '98 IDS Evaluation Program. It contains 41 features and records of various simulated attacks.
dcterms:title: NSL-KDD
